    const bank = require(&#39;./bank&#39;);

This statement will not import the Bank Model properly. In sequelize in order to import a model from a model definition you have to use `sequelize.import( // path to file)`. In order to import model correctly use following:

    const bank = sequelize.import(&#39;./bank&#39;);

**Note:** Here `seuqelize` is an instance of `Sequelize` and not the class itsself. `seuqelize` variable is the database connection you created using something like

    const sequelize = new Sequelize(DB_NAME, DB_USERNAME, DB_PASSWORD, { ...options })

